data.jamchart_notes: One of Goose's best jams ever. Starts with a Ted space and gradually moves through many different themes, both beautiful and rocking. Peaks MASSIVELY and - without missing a beat or even taking a moment to bask in the glory - segues -> to an equally good (if not better) "Echo of a Rose." Winner of JOTY 2021.

data.jamchart_notes: Beautiful Moog Muse textures dominate the first jammed version since 8/17/22.

Jazz juggernaut Julian Lage sits in and grabs immediate attention with a gorgeously improvised intro guitar solo in the second consecutive jammed out version of AWS after a 2 year absence. The lead guitarists eschew the typical sit-in dogfight by bolstering each other’s playing with creative musical underscores, offering ample room to the other to work their magic.
